article.headline: Kate Bulger leads West Virginia with 16 points in loss
article.linkText: Pondexter keys Rutgers' sixth straight victory
article.story:
PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter scored 18 points as (No.
25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) Rutgers beat West Virginia 65-50 Wednesday night.

	   The victory was the sixth straight for Rutgers (15-6, 8-2 Big
East). Mauri Horton added 14 points and Chelsea Newton 10 for the
Scarlet Knights.

	   Kate Bulger scored 16 points to lead the Mountaineers (12-9,
1-8).

	   Rutgers worked its inside game in the first half, controlling
the offensive boards to generate extra chances. An 8-0 run seven
minutes into the game gave the Scarlet Knights a nine-point lead
that increased to as much as 23 midway through the second half.

	   West Virginia cut the margin to 12 twice late in the second
half, but could get no closer.
